com.googlecode.cqengine.index.sqlite

Class SQLiteIdentityIndex<A extends Comparable<A>,O>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.googlecode.cqengine.index.sqlite.SQLiteIdentityIndex<A,O>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ModificationListener<O>, AttributeIndex<A,O>, Index<O>, IdentityAttributeIndex<A,O>, NonHeapTypeIndex, KeyStatisticsAttributeIndex<A,O>, KeyStatisticsIndex<A,O>, SortedKeyStatisticsAttributeIndex<A,O>, SortedKeyStatisticsIndex<A,O>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SQLiteDiskIdentityIndex, SQLiteOffHeapIdentityIndex

    public class SQLiteIdentityIndex<A extends Comparable<A>,O>
extends Object
implements IdentityAttributeIndex<A,O>, SortedKeyStatisticsAttributeIndex<A,O>, NonHeapTypeIndex
    An index which allows objects to be persisted directly in the index in serialized form, and to be accessed using a primary key attribute (as obtained from a foreign key held elsewhere).

    This index actually wraps an SQLiteIndex, but configures the value that it stores for each primary key, to be the actual serialized bytes of the object which has that key.

    Author:
    niall.gallagher

        public Index<O> getEffectiveIndex()
        Description copied from interface: Index
        Returns the effective index, which Persistence objects will use to determine the identity of the index making persistence requests. Most Index implementations will typically return a reference to themselves ('this'). However in advanced cases when one index delegates to another, the implementation of the wrapping index will create a subclass the delegate index, and override this method in the delegate index so that when the delegate index interacts with the persistence, it will identify itself as the outer or "effective" index.
        Specified by:
        getEffectiveIndex in interface Index<O>
